{
  "texts": [
    "The objective is, for instance, to accurately categorize a paragraph such as The patient reports pressure pain in the left chest under the section class Anamnese.",
    "To conduct PET experiments, we need a pretrained masked language model M with a vocabulary V, a few-shot dataset with training instances x i ∈ X and target labels y i ∈ Y.",
    "We further need a pattern function P that maps instances to a set of cloze sentences (templates) P: X → V *, and a verbalizer function v: Y → V that maps each label to a single token from the vocabulary of M. The PET workflow contains three basic steps (see Fig. 2): (1) applying P to each input instance x i and fine-tune a model M for each template to obtain the most likely token for the MASK token v(y), (2) use the ensemble of fine-tuned models M from the previous step and annotate a large unlabeled dataset D with soft labels, and (3) train a final classifier C with a traditional sequence classification head on the labeled dataset D.",
    "Template engineering is a crucial hyperparameter in a PET experiment.",
    "For the core experiments, we used four different template types (including examples and English translations (in brackets)):"
  ]
}